New Records: Corey Seager became the first exclusively left-handed-hitting shortstop in MLB history to reach 200 home runs.
Key Match Events: Corey Seager hit a solo home run in the 4th inning.
Nathan Eovaldi pitched seven scoreless innings with 10 strikeouts.
Others: Kirby Yates surrendered a home run to Andrew Benintendi in the 9th inning.
Wyatt Langford extended the lead with an RBI single in the 7th inning.
Nick Nastrini pitched six innings of three-hit ball in his first major league start since June 8.
